It is true that the utterance of the Divine Name can absolve one from all
sins and enable one to attain salvation ... but that is possible only when
the Name is uttered with faith and reverence and the practice is free from
all taints of sin against the Name, viz. ... ranking the Name with other
virtues and practising fasting, charity, sacrifices, etc., thinking that
